  "body": "Hey there,\n\nI'm having an issue with dangerouslySetInnerHTML and dollar signs.\nIt seems like when calling React.renderToString (server side rendering), if the __html value given to dangerouslySetInnerHTML contains \"$$123\" then it gets rendered as \"$123\". (lost a dollar sign)\n\nCould find an easy way to fix that so i've started doing this terrible thing: html.replace(/\\$\\$/g, '$$$$$'). \n",
